The deletion of one name from this list [probably Nathaniel Vincent, who was discharged at Leghorn (see next voyage, which actually preceded this one.)] seems to have caused a mixup in the listed age of some of these seamen. William Ranson is listed here as 17 and 5' 3"; elsewhere he is 34 and 6' 5", and black. I have left the original information here, but believe it to be faulty.
